[thinking] **Exploring indexing requirements**
[thinking] 
[thinking] Okay, so it looks like meaningful indexing needs an Analyzer implementation. The lucene-core package has the org.apache.lucene.analysis.Analyzer abstract class and some token attributes, but there seems to be a lack of a concrete analyzer, aside from potentially the Mock one. To index text effectively, I'd need lucene-analyzers-common. Yet, I think I could still cover lucene-core adequately, especially using StringField, although TextField requires a TokenStream. There's a lot to unpack here!
[thinking] 
[thinking] **Deciding on Maven dependencies**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I need to decide if an extra Maven dependency is necessary. Typically, Lucene core is often used with lucene-analyzers-common and queryparser, but I can focus on instantiating core-only classes without adding dependencies. It seems unwise to add an extra dependency unless it's concretely needed. Although adding StandardAnalyzer might enhance indexing, the current tests achieve satisfactory results with just the core library. I might need to check the jar manifest for additional information on dependencies.
[thinking] 
